names.alias: Class II iron-sulfur assembly complex, BOL2-GRX4

attributeList.attribute: Reversibly binds [2Fe-2S] clusters and appears to play a role in Fe-S cluster assembly and trafficking, and in transferring an intact [2Fe-2S] cluster to an apo acceptor protein. Active in the nucleo-cytoplasmic compartments.

[2Fe-2S]-bridged heterocomplex with GRX4 providing two Cys ligands from the Cys-Gly-Phe-Ser (CGSF) active site and one glutathione molecule. BOL2 provides an invariant His which serves as a cluster ligand.
